This is a known breaking change. Android 15 (API 35), which .NET 10 targets, **deprecated `SOFT_INPUT_ADJUST_RESIZE`** and enforces edge-to-edge display. The fix is to react to `WindowInsets` instead.

### Recommended approach: use `Ime` window insets

In your **Android platform code** (e.g., `Platforms/Android/MainActivity.cs`):

```csharp
using Android.Views;
using AndroidX.Core.View;
using Microsoft.Maui.Platform;

public class MainActivity : MauiAppCompatActivity
{
    protected override void OnCreate(Bundle? savedInstanceState)
    {
        base.OnCreate(savedInstanceState);

        // Edge-to-edge is now the default; just listen for insets
        ViewCompat.SetOnApplyWindowInsetsListener(
            Window!.DecorView.FindViewById(Android.Resource.Id.Content)!,
            new KeyboardInsetsListener());
    }

    private class KeyboardInsetsListener : Java.Lang.Object, IOnApplyWindowInsetsListener
    {
        public WindowInsetsCompat OnApplyWindowInsets(View view, WindowInsetsCompat insets)
        {
            var imeInsets = insets.GetInsets(WindowInsetsCompat.Type.Ime());
            var navInsets = insets.GetInsets(WindowInsetsCompat.Type.NavigationBars());

            // Use the larger of keyboard or nav-bar bottom inset
            int bottomPx = Math.Max(imeInsets.Bottom, navInsets.Bottom);

            view.SetPadding(
                view.PaddingLeft,
                view.PaddingTop,
                view.PaddingRight,
                bottomPx);

            return insets;
        }
    }
}
```

### Why this works

| .NET 9 / API ≤ 34 | .NET 10 / API 35+ |
|---|---|
| `SOFT_INPUT_ADJUST_RESIZE` shrinks the window | Deprecated & ignored |
| System handles layout shift | You react to `Ime()` insets yourself |

### Quick checklist

1. **Remove** any `App.Current.On<Android>().UseWindowSoftInputModeAdjust(…)` calls — they're no-ops now.
2. **Set** `android:windowSoftInputMode="adjustNothing"` in your `AndroidManifest.xml` (or leave it unset — the default under edge-to-edge is equivalent).
3. **Add** the insets listener above.
4. If you use a `ScrollView`, set `android:windowSoftInputMode="adjustPan"` instead — it still works and may be simpler for scroll-based layouts.

`adjustPan` is the simplest fix if your layout scrolls; the insets listener gives you full control for fixed-bottom input bars.
